de.tud.kom.p2psim.overlay.bt
Class BTClientApplication

java.lang.Object
  de.tud.kom.p2psim.impl.application.AbstractApplication
      de.tud.kom.p2psim.overlay.bt.BTClientApplication
All Implemented Interfaces:
Application, Component, OperationCallback, SupportOperations
public class BTClientApplication
extends AbstractApplication

This class represents the client application and is the top most class of the client. It has two OverlayNodes: The BTPeerSearchNode and the BTPeerDistributeNode. This class contains methods for starting a download, making this client to a seed and accessing its databus.

Author:
Jan Stolzenburg

Method Detail

downloadDocument

public void downloadDocument(BTTorrent theTorrent)
This method will start a download. You can start any number of parallel downloads. Every download will use the same BTPeerDistributionNode. It starts a BTOperationDistribute, that will start all neccessary operations for upload, download and so on.

Parameters:
theTorrent - The torrent object for the file you want to download.

listDocuments

public java.util.Collection<BTDocument> listDocuments()
Returns the list of documents this client know. The download state doesn't matter.

Returns:
the list of document this client knows.

storeDocument

public void storeDocument(BTDocument theDocument)
Use this method if you want to create a seed. This method stores the document. It keeps the state of it. If this client should be a seed, you have to set the download state of the document to "completed" or something alike.

Parameters:
theDocument -

getDataBus

public BTDataStore getDataBus()
Use this method, if you want to access the databus from outside the client. For example, if you want to manipulate some internals. But please: Be carefull!

Returns:
the data bus of this client.

createOperation

public Operation createOperation(java.lang.String opName,
                                 java.lang.String[] params,
                                 OperationCallback caller)
Description copied from interface: SupportOperations
Create an appropriate Operation. The component checks whether it can create an operation with the given name and number of parameters. This method is used only to specify operations via configuration (action) files.

Parameters:
opName - - operation name
params - - operation parameters if required.
caller - - caller Object which will be informed when the operation finishes (successfully or with a failure)
Returns:
operation - created (can be scheduled or executed immediately)
